-- EIB Studies 100 Million-Euro Loan for Cyprus City, Water Upgrade
-- B y   S a l l y   B a k e w e l l
-- 2013-03-06T17:24:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-06/eib-studies-100-million-euro-loan-for-cyprus-city-water-upgrade.html
The European Investment Bank is
considering making a loan of 100 million euros ($130 million) to
support water, sewerage and infrastructure developments in
Cyprus.  The loan would contribute to a 1.18 billion-euro project to
upgrade Cyprus’s cities, boost environmental protection and
strengthen the economy, according to a statement today on the
Luxembourg-based bank’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sally Bakewell in London at 
